# Strings / Internationalization

## Rule
All user-facing text (labels, buttons, messages, placeholders) must be placed in `client/src/strings.js` and referenced via the `S` object. Do not hardcode display strings in components.

## Usage
```js
import S from '../strings';  // or '../../strings' depending on path

// Static strings
<Typography>{S.common.save}</Typography>
<TextField label={S.auth.login.username} />

// Template with variables (use format helper)
import { format } from '../strings';
<Typography>{format(S.settings.editLabel, { label: 'Hair Types' })}</Typography>
```

## Adding New Strings
1. Add the string to `client/src/strings.js` under the appropriate section (auth, common, layout, surgeries, patients, settings, etc.).
2. Use descriptive keys: `pageTitle`, `emptyMessage`, `submitButton`, etc.
3. For templates with placeholders, use `{placeholder}` syntax: `"Remove {name} from team?"`

## Structure
- `common` — shared (Cancel, Save, Edit, Delete, Loading…)
- `auth` — login, signup, forgot password
- `layout` — nav labels (Home, Surgeries, etc.)
- `home`, `surgeries`, `patients`, `team`, `technicians`, `settings` — page-specific
- `surgeryDetail`, `report` — surgery flow
- `newSurgery`, `statusBadge`, `saveStatus`, etc.
